[{"text": "Pack your bags because ", "start": 0.0, "duration": 3.703}, {"text": "you're traveling through space", "start": 3.703, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "to see Alpha Centauri.", "start": 5.572, "duration": 3.17}, {"text": "There's just one problem.", "start": 8.742, "duration": 1.968}, {"text": "It's going to take 100 years.", "start": 10.71, "duration": 4.972}, {"text": "Is it at least possible to sleep on a trip?", "start": 15.682, "duration": 3.57}, {"text": "Yeah, but get comfy because", "start": 19.252, "duration": 3.237}, {"text": "you're going nighty-night", "start": 22.489, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "for an entire century.", "start": 24.324, "duration": 3.87}, {"text": "So what is hibernation exactly?", "start": 51.151, "duration": 4.07}, {"text": "You know, besides a really long nap?", "start": 55.221, "duration": 3.571}, {"text": "It's a prolonged resting state", "start": 58.792, "duration": 2.702}, {"text": "that animals enter", "start": 61.494, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "during winter months", "start": 62.862, "duration": 1.335}, {"text": "or when food gets scarce.", "start": 64.197, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "During hibernation,", "start": 66.9, "duration": 1.301}, {"text": "an animal\u2019s body temperature,", "start": 68.201, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "heart rate and metabolism decrease.", "start": 70.27, "duration": 3.77}, {"text": "A lot.", "start": 74.04, "duration": 1.435}, {"text": "That's because the animal's body enters", "start": 75.475, "duration": 3.07}, {"text": "a torpor state.", "start": 78.545, "duration": 2.235}, {"text": "It's a deep sleep when the animal is", "start": 80.78, "duration": 3.17}, {"text": "almost entirely inactive.", "start": 83.95, "duration": 3.07}, {"text": "Like me, at the end of the day.", "start": 87.02, "duration": 2.903}, {"text": "Now look,", "start": 89.923, "duration": 0.8}, {"text": "I don't blame you", "start": 90.723, "duration": 0.901}, {"text": "for wanting to sleep through the winter.", "start": 91.624, "duration": 1.936}, {"text": "But 100 years in space", "start": 93.56, "duration": 3.27}, {"text": "is another story entirely.", "start": 96.83, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "How would you even pull it off?", "start": 99.499, "duration": 2.836}, {"text": "First, you'd have to induce hibernation,", "start": 102.335, "duration": 3.237}, {"text": "which might get tricky.", "start": 105.572, "duration": 2.602}, {"text": "See, lowering human body", "start": 108.174, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "temperature is harder", "start": 110.243, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "than you might think.", "start": 112.011, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "Researchers think that", "start": 113.379, "duration": 1.235}, {"text": "because of our body mass,", "start": 114.614, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "we wouldn't be able to lower our body", "start": 116.783, "duration": 2.202}, {"text": "temperature to 0 \u00b0C (32 \u00b0F)", "start": 118.985, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "as rodents do.", "start": 121.454, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "It turns out we're more like bears,", "start": 123.389, "duration": 2.77}, {"text": "as our temperature only declines slightly.", "start": 126.159, "duration": 4.137}, {"text": "But you might have a workaround.", "start": 130.296, "duration": 3.671}, {"text": "Have you heard of the process", "start": 133.967, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "called cooling?", "start": 135.368, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "Hospitals use it to slow down ", "start": 137.07, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "or stop the body's functions", "start": 139.172, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "during some surgeries.", "start": 141.074, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "Ice packs, coolers", "start": 143.243, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "or even a cooled saline solution directly", "start": 145.011, "duration": 3.871}, {"text": "injected into your blood", "start": 148.882, "duration": 1.701}, {"text": "can lower your temperature.", "start": 150.583, "duration": 2.202}, {"text": "Then, you enter that torpor state", "start": 152.785, "duration": 2.87}, {"text": "we talked about before.", "start": 155.655, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "But here's the problem.", "start": 157.59, "duration": 2.57}, {"text": "We can only cool humans ", "start": 160.16, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "for 14 days, tops.", "start": 162.162, "duration": 3.169}, {"text": "So how do we keep you nice and", "start": 165.331, "duration": 2.937}, {"text": "cozy for the other 36,000?", "start": 168.268, "duration": 4.437}, {"text": "When you freeze,", "start": 172.705, "duration": 1.435}, {"text": "ice crystals form deep inside your cells.", "start": 174.14, "duration": 3.971}, {"text": "Once formed, these cell cycles", "start": 178.111, "duration": 2.602}, {"text": "can rupture and cause permanent damage.", "start": 180.713, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "To get around this, ", "start": 184.15, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "we\u2019ll need to bring out the big guns.", "start": 185.852, "duration": 2.803}, {"text": "Cryogenics.", "start": 188.655, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "This process involves", "start": 190.59, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "replacing your regular body fluids", "start": 192.192, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "with an anti-freezing agent.", "start": 194.961, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "And you know what?", "start": 197.73, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "It might work.", "start": 199.732, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "Scientists have used this technology", "start": 201.534, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "to freeze and,", "start": 203.87, "duration": 1.168}, {"text": "more importantly,", "start": 205.038, "duration": 0.867}, {"text": "unfreeze 50 mm (2 in) of tissue", "start": 205.905, "duration": 2.97}, {"text": "without causing any damage.", "start": 208.875, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "Let's say we\u2019ve got a cryogenic", "start": 212.078, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "setup on the ship.", "start": 214.547, "duration": 1.669}, {"text": "Would it allow you to survive", "start": 216.216, "duration": 1.968}, {"text": "your 100-year journey?", "start": 218.184, "duration": 3.771}, {"text": "Research shows that animals", "start": 221.955, "duration": 2.435}, {"text": "who spend more time hibernating", "start": 224.39, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "tend to live longer.", "start": 226.759, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "Yeah.", "start": 228.995, "duration": 1.168}, {"text": "Hibernation could slow aging.", "start": 230.163, "duration": 3.937}, {"text": "If that's the case,", "start": 234.1, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "you'd wake up in a new century.", "start": 235.768, "duration": 3.337}, {"text": "Technology would have advanced, ", "start": 239.105, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "societies would have evolved", "start": 241.14, "duration": 2.403}, {"text": "and the environment would have changed.", "start": 243.543, "duration": 3.87}, {"text": "When you woke up,", "start": 247.413, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "you'd be in a completely different world", "start": 249.015, "duration": 3.237}, {"text": "that you may not recognize or understand.", "start": 252.252, "duration": 4.471}, {"text": "Think about it.", "start": 256.723, "duration": 0.834}, {"text": "In the last 100 years,", "start": 257.557, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "we saw the invention of talking movies,", "start": 259.592, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "penicillin, helicopters,", "start": 262.228, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "nuclear bombs,", "start": 263.763, "duration": 0.901}, {"text": "credit cards,", "start": 264.664, "duration": 0.667}, {"text": "seat belts, computers and the internet.", "start": 265.331, "duration": 3.237}, {"text": "Wait, when were seat belts invented?", "start": 268.568, "duration": 3.503}, {"text": "Wow, 1959.", "start": 272.071, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "So we created the nuclear bomb", "start": 274.44, "duration": 3.571}, {"text": "before seat belts?", "start": 278.011, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "Okay.", "start": 280.28, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": " A lot of stuff will change,", "start": 282.048, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "and the Earth won\u2019t be", "start": 284.284, "duration": 2.435}, {"text": "exactly like you remember it.", "start": 286.719, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "If there still is an Earth.", "start": 288.888, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "As climate change continues, ", "start": 290.757, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "more and more environmental disasters", "start": 292.692, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "will occur. ", "start": 295.461, "duration": 1.669}, {"text": "Before you went into hibernation,", "start": 297.13, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "you were going to travel", "start": 298.498, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "to another planet.", "start": 299.899, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "Well, at least you won\u2019t have to deal", "start": 301.734, "duration": 1.936}, {"text": "with Earth's climate change, I guess.", "start": 303.67, "duration": 3.069}, {"text": "But if I'm being honest,", "start": 306.739, "duration": 2.436}, {"text": "I don't think you'd survive the trip.", "start": 309.175, "duration": 2.903}, {"text": "You\u2019re just not built for it.", "start": 312.078, "duration": 3.27}, {"text": "Your body doesn't have the same", "start": 315.348, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "physiological adaptations", "start": 317.617, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "that allow animals", "start": 319.652, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "to maintain a state of torpor.", "start": 321.187, "duration": 2.903}, {"text": "In reality,", "start": 324.09, "duration": 0.934}, {"text": "attempting to hibernate like an animal", "start": 325.024, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "could be super dangerous.", "start": 328.027, "duration": 2.67}, {"text": "For example,", "start": 330.697, "duration": 1.301}, {"text": "a bear eats a large amount of food", "start": 331.998, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "before hibernating,", "start": 334.701, "duration": 1.067}, {"text": "which allows it to store", "start": 335.768, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "enough energy to survive the winter.", "start": 337.737, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "If you tried to do the same thing,", "start": 340.74, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "your artery walls would thicken", "start": 343.743, "duration": 2.202}, {"text": "and give you a big list of health problems.", "start": 345.945, "duration": 3.737}, {"text": "A bear can remain", "start": 349.682, "duration": 1.468}, {"text": "completely still for months,", "start": 351.15, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "but you would lose", "start": 353.252, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "muscle mass and strength", "start": 355.154, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "after just a week or two of inactivity.", "start": 357.023, "duration": 3.17}, {"text": "This is why bedridden patients often", "start": 360.193, "duration": 2.569}, {"text": "suffer from muscle atrophy and weakness.", "start": 362.762, "duration": 4.237}, {"text": "So we've still got some work to do", "start": 366.999, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "before you can pull this off.", "start": 369.535, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "We humans just aren't", "start": 372.004, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "made to sleep that long.", "start": 373.706, "duration": 2.302}, {"text": "But what if you took", "start": 376.008, "duration": 2.37}, {"text": "that as a personal challenge?", "start": 378.378, "duration": 2.535}, {"text": "What if you stopped sleeping entirely?", "start": 380.913, "duration": 4.572}, {"text": "Well, that's a story", "start": 385.485, "duration": 2.969}, {"text": "for another WHAT IF.", "start": 388.454, "duration": 2.403}]